summary: This document is an FBI electronic communication and related forms detailing the service of a grand jury subpoena to a witness (name redacted) in New York on May 29, 2008, for testimony regarding the Jeffrey Epstein investigation. It includes the subpoena, return of service, witness travel instructions, and a summary of the agents' interaction with the witness, who requested her attorney and was informed the matter concerned Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: A witness was subpoenaed on May 29, 2008, to testify before a federal grand jury in West Palm Beach regarding the Jeffrey Epstein investigation.
The witness immediately requested her attorney, Diarmuid White, and was informed by FBI agents that she was not a target of the investigation.
The FBI agent explicitly told the witness the interview was regarding Jeffrey Epstein, and asked if she was familiar with him, to which she replied 'OK...'.
The document includes detailed instructions for fact witnesses regarding travel arrangements and reimbursement, indicating standard DOJ procedures for witness management.
The investigation is formally titled to include both Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine N. Maxwell concerning 'WSTA - CHILD PROSTITUTION'.
